headline: Rate cuts would be boon for 2026 retail spending: Goldman Sachs
summary: Goldman Sachs will hear from top executives and retail leaders at its 32nd Annual Global Retailing Conference later this week. Goldman Sachs US retail analyst in global investment research Kate McShane shares her 2026 forecast for US consumer spending with Josh Lipton and what interest rate cuts could mean for lower and middle-income Americans. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination.

headline: Elevation Point Announces Strategic Collaboration with Goldman Sachs to Help Elite Partner Firms Thrive in Independence
summary: Elevation Point, a growth accelerator and minority stake partner for independent advisors, today announced a strategic collaboration with Goldman Sachs to offer its partner firms access to Goldman Sachs' banking and lending, trading, asset management and capital markets capabilities. The collaboration also expands an existing agreement with Goldman Sachs Custody Solutions ("GSCS"), a modern custodial provider for independent advisors, which will now serve as a key custodian for Elevation Point.

headline: Goldman Sachs Sees Pickup in M&A Deals Toward End of 2025
summary: Christina Minnis, Goldman Sachs' head of global credit finance and global acquisition finance, says credit remains an important asset class and mergers and acquisitions activity will continue to improve. "What we see in terms of corporate boardrooms and sponsor willingness to transact is really picking up," Minnis tells Bloomberg Television. "We're quite optimistic about the end of '25 and into '26." She also discusses the outlook for artificial intelligence and the datacenters and other infrastructure that surrounds the industry.
